<p>I'm using Formtastic as a semantic_form_for books and lists. Each list <code>has_many</code> books and each book <code>belongs_to</code> a list. When the user creates a new book, they can choose what list to add the book to. Here is my form code:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;%= semantic_form_for(@book) do |f| %&gt;     &lt;p&gt;Select a list to add this book to: &lt;/p&gt;     &lt;%= f.input :list, :as =&gt; :select %&gt;     ...     &lt;%= f.submit "Add book", class: "btn btn-default" %&gt; &lt;% end %&gt; </code></pre>  <p>The only problem is that the select tag that is generated has a blank option for select at the top. So the options for select look like this:</p>  <ul> <li>[blank]</li> <li>List 1</li> <li>List 2</li> <li><p>List 3</p>  <p>etc.</p></li> </ul>  <p>I don't want there to be an extra space. How can I fix that?</p>  <p>Here is a picture:</p>  <p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/b0xlp.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/b0xlp.png" alt="enter image description here"></a></p>